# Copy this file to ".env" and fill in real values, OR export these variables
# in your shell before running `./gradlew bootRun`.
#
# Where to get them:
#   - ADYEN_API_KEY:         Customer Area (TEST) > Developers > API credentials > [your merchant] > Generate API key
#   - ADYEN_CLIENT_KEY:      Same page as API key. Add http://localhost:8080 to Allowed origins.
#                            For ngrok also add: https://<your-ngrok-domain>.ngrok-free.dev
#   - ADYEN_MERCHANT_ACCOUNT: The name of your merchant account (usually ends with -ECOM)
#   - ADYEN_HMAC_KEY:        Customer Area > Developers > Webhooks > [your webhook] > Generate HMAC key
#                            (you only need this for Step 16+)
#
# Webhook tunnel (for Step 16+):
#   We use a reserved ngrok dev domain so the URL is stable across restarts.
#   Start the tunnel with:   ./scripts/ngrok.sh
#   Configured domain:       coolingly-supercretaceous-branden.ngrok-free.dev
#   Webhook URL for Adyen:   https://coolingly-supercretaceous-branden.ngrok-free.dev/webhooks

ADYEN_API_KEY=
ADYEN_CLIENT_KEY=
ADYEN_MERCHANT_ACCOUNT=
ADYEN_HMAC_KEY=
